page.title: 14Life-styles
page.content: " Life in Deene starts early.Our cowman arrives from Corby at 5am.He fetches the cows from the field.If it is mushroom time he's likely to meet one of the Barratt family collecting their breakfast. The remaining men who work at Home Farm or on the Deene Estate start work at 8am.This is a busy time in the main street with tractors and implements travelling to their work.Between 8am & 9am cars come through the village on their way to the new Industrial Estate in Corby. Mornings and afternoons are very quiet. On Mon.the library van visits,on Thurs. the refuse is collected,and milk is delivered every other day.A dormobile collects one boy who goes to school in Kingscliffe."......Mrs P.Reading of Manor Farm, Deene.
